The circumstance l have just mentioned raises a presumption that - the attribution of the ‘Dicit Dominus Ego cogito' to the twenty-fifth Sunday is unauthentic, and that this antiphonarial indication, like that for the following Sunday, like that for the eighteenth of the post- pentecostal group, like that for the second in Lent, like others which l need not now enumerate, was taken, not from the original liber massalis, but from some other book3 in other words, that, whilst the mass is authentic‚ the antiphonarial indication appended to its title is of alien derivation. .
